{
  "text": "Subacromial impingement syndrome is a complication often seen after surgical treatment of proximal humerus fractures. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] In various studies in literature, the frequency has been reported as 2%-7%. [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] In the geriatric patient group in particular, impingement syndrome may sometimes severely restrict daily living activities. [CITATION_6] Removal of the implant may be required in treatment. [CITATION_7] Brunner et al reported that it was necessary to remove the implant in 3 patients of a series of 15. [CITATION_8] In the current series, subacromial impingement syndrome developed in 2 patients. Of these, the implant was removed in 1 and the complaints recovered and in the other case, the recommendation of implant removal was not accepted by the patient.",
  "correct_citation": {
